Animated GIF/WebP initial-load optimization
===========================================

Date: 2026-07-02

Purpose
-------
Reduce animated GIF and animated WebP initial loading time without changing the
animation playback architecture.

The previous bundled helper was a PyInstaller one-file executable. It worked on
fresh Windows installs, but each launch paid the one-file self-extract/startup
cost. This change adds a PyInstaller onedir helper runtime and updates Quivi's
animation loader to prefer it, while leaving the one-file helper as a fallback.

Changed files
-------------
- library.zip
  - Updated pyfreeimage/image.pyc.
  - The animation loader now prefers:
    1. webp_extract_pillow_runtime/webp_extract_pillow/webp_extract_pillow.exe
    2. webp_extract_pillow.exe
    3. webp_extract_pillow.py via python/pythonw
  - Added optional QUIVI_ANIM_PROFILE timing support. It is silent unless the
    environment variable is set.

- webp_extract_pillow.py
  - Added optional QUIVI_ANIM_PROFILE timing output to profile.txt in the helper
    output directory.
  - Tracks total, seek, convert, and BMP save time.

- webp_extract_pillow_runtime/webp_extract_pillow/
  - New self-contained PyInstaller onedir helper runtime.
  - Runtime size: 62 files, 29,501,578 bytes.

- webp_extract_pillow.exe
  - Kept as the fallback one-file helper.
  - Hash is unchanged from the before-helper-onedir backup.

