Notes
-----
This removes most of the avoidable helper startup overhead while preserving the
current predecode-to-BMP flow. The remaining load time is mostly actual Pillow
decode/convert/save work, so further major gains would likely require a larger
structural change such as caching decoded frames between sessions, decoding into
a faster intermediate format, or integrating the decoder more directly into the
viewer process.
